sfpsUnresolveTableAPIAgeOutTime.name: sfpsUnresolveTableAPIAgeOutTime
sfpsUnresolveTableAPIAgeOutTime.description: The age out time in minutes in which entries in the sfpsUnresolveTable are deleted. Any entry in which sysUpTime minus last miss time is greater than this value is deleted from the table.

sfpsUnresolveTableStatsAvgReqTime.name: sfpsUnresolveTableStatsAvgReqTime
sfpsUnresolveTableStatsAvgReqTime.description: The average time in 10 msec units between unresolved requests seen by the server.

sfpsBlockResolveTable.name: sfpsBlockResolveTable
sfpsBlockResolveTable.description: This table contains a list of address objects whose resolve requests are being blocked for a given time period by the Block Resolve Server. The Block Resolve Server is actually a 'leaky bucket' server that will slow down high frequency resolve requests for addresses that remain unresolved. Resolve requests are sent through the system at a slower user configurable rate.

sfpsBlockResolveTableHash.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableHash
sfpsBlockResolveTableHash.description: A hash of the address object value contained in this entry's sfpsBlockResolveTableAOValue

sfpsBlockResolveTableHashIndex.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableHashIndex
sfpsBlockResolveTableHashIndex.description: An index into the hash bucket

sfpsBlockResolveTableAOType.description: The address object type of this entry

sfpsBlockResolveTableAOValue.description: The address object value of the entry.

sfpsBlockResolveTableStartTime.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableStartTime
sfpsBlockResolveTableStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when blocking of this request object was started.

sfpsBlockResolveTableNumBlocked.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableNumBlocked
sfpsBlockResolveTableNumBlocked.description: The number of times a resolve request for this address object was blocked resulting in the deletion of the call.

sfpsBlockResolveTableNumSent.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableNumSent
sfpsBlockResolveTableNumSent.description: The number of times a resolve request for this address object was sent through the system.

sfpsBlockResolveTableLastSeen.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableLastSeen
sfpsBlockResolveTableLastSeen.description: The value of sysUpTime when the most recent resolve request was seen by the Block Resolve Server.

sfpsBlockResolveTableAvgPeriod.name: sfpsBlockResolveTableAvgPeriod
sfpsBlockResolveTableAvgPeriod.description: The average period in seconds between resolve requests for this address object since sfpsBlockResolveTableStartTime

sfpsBlockResolveAPIVerb.name: sfpsBlockResolveAPIVerb
sfpsBlockResolveAPIVerb.description: When set, the corresponding action is taken. For add-entry, an entry is added to sfpsBlockResolveTable for the given sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOType and sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOValue. For del-entry, an entry is deleted from the sfpsBlockResolveTable. For set-parameter, the most recent sets of sfpsBlockResolveAPITestCount, sfpsBlockResolveAPIThreshold, sfpsBlockResolveAPISendPeriod are applied.

sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOType.name: sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOType
sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOType.description: The address object type specified by a well-known string to be used in the next Verb action.

sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOValue.name: sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOValue
sfpsBlockResolveAPIAOValue.description: The address object value to be used in the next Verb action.

sfpsBlockResolveAPITestCount.name: sfpsBlockResolveAPITestCount
sfpsBlockResolveAPITestCount.description: The number of unknown resolve requests seen before a test is made to determine whether further resolve requests should be blocked or not. Block tests are made on address objects every 'N' resolve requests that fail where 'N' equals the value of this object.

sfpsBlockResolveAPIThreshold.name: sfpsBlockResolveAPIThreshold
sfpsBlockResolveAPIThreshold.description: The average number of seconds per resolve request for a given address object that will trigger a block. This value is used in conjunction with sfpsBlockResolveAPITestCount to perform block tests on unresolved address objects. If the period between unresolved requests is less than or equal to this value, then the resolve request is blocked.

sfpsBlockResolveAPISendPeriod.name: sfpsBlockResolveAPISendPeriod
sfpsBlockResolveAPISendPeriod.description: The number of seconds between resolve requests that will be sent through the system.

sfpsBlockResolveStatsNumEntries.name: sfpsBlockResolveStatsNumEntries
sfpsBlockResolveStatsNumEntries.description: The number of entries in sfpsBlockResolveTable.

sfpsBlockResolveStatsTableSize.name: sfpsBlockResolveStatsTableSize
sfpsBlockResolveStatsTableSize.description: The maximum number of entries allowed in sfpsBlockResolveTable.

sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalReqSeen.name: sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalReqSeen
sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalReqSeen.description: The total number of resolve requests the Block Resolve Server has seen. This value does not include inter-switch resolves.

sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalBlocked.name: sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalBlocked
sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalBlocked.description: The total number of resolve requests that have been blocked by the server.

sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalSent.name: sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalSent
sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalSent.description: The total number of requests sent through the system for address objects that are being blocked.

sfpsBlockResolveStatsAvgReqTime.name: sfpsBlockResolveStatsAvgReqTime
sfpsBlockResolveStatsAvgReqTime.description: The average time in 10 msec units between resolve requests seen by the server. It is computed by dividing sysUpTime by sfpsBlockResolveStatsTotalReqSeen.
